  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nThe Jaeger client of a component utilizing the quarkus-jaeger extension fails to retrieve sampler strategies from a remote host.\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWhen setting the *quarkus.jaeger.sampler-manager-host-port* property to a value of `my-jaeger-agent:5778`, then the Jaeger client retrieves the sampler strategies from that host and uses them during runtime.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nThe Jaeger client does not retrieve the sampling strategies from the configured host and also does not log any error.\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\nLinux luke 5.13.0-28-generic #31-Ubuntu SMP Thu Jan 13 17:41:06 UTC 2022 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\nopenjdk version \"17.0.1\" 2021-10-19 OpenJDK Runtime Environment (build 17.0.1+12-Ubuntu-121.10) OpenJDK 64-Bit Server VM (build 17.0.1+12-Ubuntu-121.10, mixed mode, sharing)\n\n### GraalVM version (if different from Java)\n\n21.3.1\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\n2.6.3\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional information\n\nThe problem seems to be in the *JaegerDeploymentRecorder* class' *initTracerConfig* method where the `JAEGER_SAMPLER_MANAGER_HOST_PORT` system property is set to *InetAddress.toString()* which yields an invalid value like `my-jaeger-host/<unresolved>:5778`.\r\n",
